SARA WRITE UP --- 
1. One person should create a Main Repository in github; then invite any collaboraters.
2. Everyone (including the creator of the main repository) should branch the Main Repository so they can work on their own codes and then do pull requests. 
3. Once you have created your branch, open Visual Studio Code. Login into RON using ron.sr.unh.edu (ssh username@ron.sr.unh.edu).
4. Clone your branch in VScode 
    git clone -b BranchName  --single-branch https://github.com/githubUSERNAME/Repository Name
      EX. git clone -b SaraBranch  --single-branch https://github.com/ssunhbio/GEN811_16s
5. Use FileZilla to transfer your raw data from the source company to your new RON branch.
6. Activate a conda environment.
    conda activate
7. You can use conda list or conda info --envs to see the environments available to use.  We will use qiime2-amplicon-2024.5 for trimming our runs.
    conda activate qiime2-amplicon-2024.5
8. qiime2 has cutadapt in it, which we can activate the same way we activated conda and qiime2
    conda activate cutadapt4.9
